# Main-Only Workflow (no feature branches)

This repository uses a **single-branch (`main`) workflow**. The user has
explicitly opted out of feature branches.

## Rules

1. **Never create branches.** Do not run `git checkout -b`, `git branch
   <name>`, `git switch -c`, or `git worktree add`. All work happens on
   `main`.
2. **Commit directly to `main`.** When the user asks you to commit, stage
   and commit on `main`.
3. **Push `main`.** When the user asks you to push, push `main` to
   `origin` directly.
4. **Existing branches:** if a feature branch already exists, merge it
   into `main` (fast-forward when possible) and delete the branch
   (local and remote). Do not leave stray branches behind.
5. **This overrides** any general "branch first before committing to the
   default branch" guidance. The `no-destructive-git` rule still
   applies (never destroy uncommitted/untracked work).
6. After pushing `main`, still **monitor GitHub Actions** for that
   commit per `post-push-github-actions-monitor.mdc`.
